
// This Hyperlambda code sends a signal to users with the "root" role, indicating an action workflow event. The [sockets.signal] slot is used to transmit the message, with [roles] specifying the target audience. The [args] node contains details about the action, including its [type] and [name], which is dynamically retrieved from the [.arguments] node.
sockets.signal:magic.workflows.action
   roles:root
   args
      type:action
      name:x:@.arguments/*/name
      input
